1. *Uđemo* li zajedno u restoran ili ćemo se naći tamo? (Will we enter the restaurant together or will we meet there?)
2. Ona će nas sačekati dok *uđemo* u stan. (She will wait for us until we enter the apartment.)
3. Ako *uđemo* u probleme, obratimo se policiji. (If we get into trouble, let's turn to the police.)
4. Da bismo *ušli* u zgradu, moramo upisati kod na ulaznim vratima. (In order to enter the building, we have to enter the code on the entrance door.)
5. Oni *ulaze* u kupovinu baš u trenutku kada smo prolazili pored prodavnice. (They were entering the store just as we were passing by.)
6. Mogu *ući* u klub samo ako imam člansku kartu. (I can only enter the club if I have a membership card.)
7. Kada *budemo ušli* u grad, posetićemo nekoliko muzeja. (When we enter the city, we will visit several museums.)
8. *Ušli* smo u autobus i odmah pronašli slobodna sedišta. (We entered the bus and immediately found empty seats.)
9. Moramo *ući* u trag lopovu i vratiti ukradene stvari. (We have to track down the thief and return the stolen items.)
10. Oni su se *uvukli* u kuću kada je počela kiša. (They snuck into the house when it started raining.)